      <p class="text-secondary mb-0">The Sit-in Monitoring System for CCS Laboratories is designed to efficiently manage and monitor student laboratory usage within the College of Computer Studies. This system allows students to log their sit-in sessions and enables laboratory staff to track attendance, monitor computer usage, and maintain accurate records of laboratory activities. By digitalizing the monitoring process, the system helps improve organization, accountability, and security in the laboratory while providing a convenient and reliable way to manage sit-in schedules and student access.</p>
